"{\n    \"Title\": \"Notes to the financial statementsMarch 31, 2018\",\n    \"row 1\": \"9. Credit facility\",\n    \"row 2\": \"In 2015, the Corporation secured a revolving credit facility which provides for a maximum borrowing amount of $40 million. The\",\n    \"row 3\": \"facility bears interest at the Canadian Prime less 0.25%. The interest rate was 3.20% at March 31, 2018 (2017 - 2.45%). The\",\n    \"row 4\": \"facility is secured by a first lien interest over several of the Corporation's real properties in the City of Toronto and a General\",\n    \"row 5\": \"Security Agreement creating a first priority interest over property of the Corporation not obtained through a contribution\",\n    \"row 6\": \" agreement, including accounts receivable. At March 31, 2018, the available borrowing limit is $37 million as a result of a Letter of\",\n    \"row 7\": \"Credit issued by Waterfront Toronto during the year to the Department of Fisheries and Oceans for the Cherry Street Stormwater\",\n    \"row 8\": \"and Lakefilling project.\",\n    \"row 9\": \"Under the current financing agreement, the Corporation is subject to a financial covenant. The revolving credit facility stipulates\",\n    \"row 10\": \"- that the Corporation must ensure that the most recent appraised value of the properties which secure the facility at all times\",\n    \"row 11\": \"provide a minimum of 150% coverage for the outstanding amount of credit. As at March 31, 2018, the Corporation is in\",\n    \"row 12\": \"compliance with this covenant and expects to be in compliance for the next 12 months.\",\n    \"row 13\": \"10. Accounts payable and accrued liabilities \",\n    \"row 14\": \"March 31, March 31,\",\n    \"row 15\": \"2018 2017\",\n    \"row 16\": \"Accrued liabilities 17,946,776 5,555,936\",\n    \"row 17\": \"Accounts payable 2,905,404 1,047,093 -\",\n    \"row 18\": \"Holdbacks payable 996,635 97,460\",\n    \"row 19\": \". 21,848,815 6,700,489\",\n    \"row 20\": \"eens erence e